   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE ONE BODY Scripture Reading: Eph 4:3-6 OUTLINE One God Triune Gen 1:1.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>One incarnation God mingling Himself with man John 1:1, 14.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>One Christ in His incarnation Matt 1:16.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>One crucifixion: Terminating the old creation Rom 6:6.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Dealing with Satan, the world, sin, and all negative things Heb 2:14; John 12:31; 1:29; Eph 2:15-16; Col 2:14.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>One resurrection: Germinating the new creation.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Begetting Christ in His humanity to be the firstborn Son of God Acts 13:33; Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Making Christ the last Adam the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Regenerating all the believers in Christ to be the many sons of God 1 Pet 1:3; Heb 2:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>One Christ in His ascension Acts 2:32-36.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>One Body of Christ: The fullness, the expression, of the One who fills all in all Eph 1:23.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The organism of the processed and consummated Triune God Eph 3:17-19.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Constituted with all the members of Christ Rom 12:5; 1 Cor 10:17.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>One new man Eph 2:15; Col 3:10-11: Christ is all the members of this one new man.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Christ is in all the members of this one new man.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>For the accomplishment of God's eternal economy Eph 3:8-10.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>One church of God Eph 1:22; 1 Cor 10:32b: Manifested in many localities Rev 1:11.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>As many local churches Rev 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The local churches: Many in existence.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Still one Body universally in element Eph 4:4.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The secret in practicality: The one accord in the local churches Phil 1:27b; 2:2.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The oneness in the universal Body Eph 4:3; John 17:11, 21-23.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The unique relationship, fellowship, and blending of all the local churches: As much as practicality allows.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Without boundaries of states, provinces, or nations.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The clustering and the moving together of neighboring churches: As much as possible.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Without the abolishing of the local administrations in business affairs.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The practices of the Lord and the apostle: The Lord's blending the seven churches in Asia into one by sending them one total epistle respectively and collectively with the whole book of Revelation Rev 1:4, 11; chs.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>2 3.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The apostle Paul's blending the two churches in Colossae and Laodicea as one by sending them epistles in common Col 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The apostle Paul's practice of the fellowship of the Body among the churches in his greetings Rom 16:1-16, 20-24.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>All the local churches on the entire globe should be absolutely one: By being: In the oneness of the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>In the one accord of our spirit, soul, and mind.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>In the realm of: The growth of life for the testimony of Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The preaching of the gospel.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The spreading of the Lord's recovery.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The building up of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The accomplishment of God's eternal economy.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>For the Lord's move in His recovery both locally and universally, we all need to be: Body-conscious in one accord.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Body-centered in oneness.</S>
   </TEXT>
